{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":346,"text":"What do you guys think?"},{"time":2706,"text":"For those who watched\nSir Ken's memorable TED Talk,"},{"time":7180,"text":"I am a typical example \nof what he describes"},{"time":10322,"text":"as \"the body as a form\nof transport for the head,\""},{"time":13346,"text":"a university professor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15737,"text":"You might think it was not fair"},{"time":19217,"text":"that I've been lined up to speak\nafter these first two talks"},{"time":22180,"text":"to speak about science."},{"time":24774,"text":"I can't move my body to the beat,"},{"time":28272,"text":"and after a scientist\nwho became a philosopher,"},{"time":31184,"text":"I have to talk about hard science."},{"time":33126,"text":"It could be a very dry subject."},{"time":36154,"text":"Yet, I feel honored."},{"time":39679,"text":"Never in my career,"},{"time":41462,"text":"and it's been a long career,"},{"time":43023,"text":"have I had the opportunity to start a talk"},{"time":45256,"text":"feeling so inspired, like this one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48264,"text":"Usually, talking about science"},{"time":52144,"text":"is like exercising in a dry place."},{"time":56284,"text":"However, I've had the pleasure"},{"time":59516,"text":"of being invited to come here\nto talk about water."},{"time":63885,"text":"The words \"water\" and \"dry\"\ndo not match, right?"},{"time":67426,"text":"It is even better to talk about\nwater in the Amazon,"},{"time":70916,"text":"which is the splendid cradle \nof life. Fresh life."},{"time":75950,"text":"So this is what inspired me."},{"time":78028,"text":"That's why I'm here,\nalthough I'm carrying"},{"time":80230,"text":"my head over here."},{"time":82143,"text":"I am trying, or will try to convey\nthis inspiration."},{"time":86237,"text":"I hope this story will inspire you\nand that you'll spread the word."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91317,"text":"We know that there is controversy."},{"time":95637,"text":"The Amazon is the \"lung of the world,\""},{"time":98940,"text":"because of its massive power\nto have vital gases exchanged"},{"time":104426,"text":"between the forest and the atmosphere."},{"time":106245,"text":"We also hear about\nthe storehouse of biodiversity."},{"time":110345,"text":"While many believe it,"},{"time":114651,"text":"few know it."},{"time":116197,"text":"If you go out there, in this marsh,"},{"time":118075,"text":"you'll be amazed at the --"},{"time":121913,"text":"You can barely see the animals."},{"time":123957,"text":"The Indians say, \"The forest\nhas more eyes than leaves.\""},{"time":128011,"text":"That is true, and I will try\nto show you something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130987,"text":"But today, I'm going to use\na different approach,"},{"time":134168,"text":"one that is inspired by these\ntwo initiatives here,"},{"time":137188,"text":"a harmonic one and a philosophical one."},{"time":139869,"text":"I'll try to use an approach\nthat's slightly materialistic,"},{"time":143998,"text":"but it also attempts to convey\nthat, in nature, there is"},{"time":147216,"text":"extraordinary philosophy and harmony."},{"time":150310,"text":"There'll be no music in my presentation,"},{"time":152271,"text":"but I hope you'll all notice the music\nof the reality I'm going to show you."},{"time":156494,"text":"I'm going to talk about physiology —\nnot about lungs,"},{"time":159107,"text":"but other analogies with human physiology,"},{"time":162635,"text":"especially the heart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164744,"text":"We'll start"},{"time":169132,"text":"by thinking that water is like blood."},{"time":174500,"text":"The circulation in our body\ndistributes fresh blood,"},{"time":179349,"text":"which feeds, nurtures and supports us,"},{"time":181959,"text":"and brings the used blood back\nto be renewed."},{"time":186337,"text":"In the Amazon, things happen similarly."},{"time":190659,"text":"We'll start by talking about\nthe power of all these processes."},{"time":195766,"text":"This is an image"},{"time":200387,"text":"of rain in motion."},{"time":203198,"text":"What you see there\nis the years passing in seconds."},{"time":207211,"text":"Rains all over the world.\nWhat do you see?"},{"time":210159,"text":"The equatorial region, in general,"},{"time":212019,"text":"and the Amazon specifically,"},{"time":213882,"text":"is extremely important\nfor the world's climate."},{"time":216751,"text":"It's a powerful engine."},{"time":218916,"text":"There is a frantic evaporation\ntaking place here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224212,"text":"If we take a look at this other image,"},{"time":226834,"text":"which shows the water vapor flow,"},{"time":229616,"text":"you have dry air in black,\nmoist air in gray,"},{"time":232801,"text":"and clouds in white."},{"time":234232,"text":"What you see there is an extraordinary\nresurgence in the Amazon."},{"time":239908,"text":"What phenomenon -- if it's not a desert,"},{"time":242031,"text":"what phenomenon makes water\ngush from the ground into the atmosphere"},{"time":247277,"text":"with such power \nthat it can be seen from space?"},{"time":250360,"text":"What phenomenon is this?"},{"time":251902,"text":"It could be a geyser."},{"time":254770,"text":"A geyser is underground water\nheated by magma,"},{"time":258558,"text":"exploding into the atmosphere"},{"time":259998,"text":"and transferring this water \ninto the atmosphere."},{"time":263668,"text":"There are no geysers in the Amazon,\nunless I am wrong."},{"time":266534,"text":"I don't know of any."},{"time":268502,"text":"But we have something\nthat plays the same role,"},{"time":272906,"text":"with much more elegance though:"},{"time":276298,"text":"the trees, our good old friends"},{"time":279194,"text":"that, like geysers,"},{"time":282008,"text":"can transfer an enormous amount of water\nfrom the ground into the atmosphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287086,"text":"There are 600 billion trees\nin the Amazon forest, 600 billion geysers."},{"time":292783,"text":"That is done with\nan extraordinary sophistication."},{"time":296646,"text":"They don't need the heat of magma."},{"time":298291,"text":"They use sunlight to do this process."},{"time":301262,"text":"So, in a typical sunny day in the Amazon,"},{"time":304793,"text":"a big tree manages\nto transfer 1,000 liters of water"},{"time":307723,"text":"through its transpiration --"},{"time":310032,"text":"1,000 liters."},{"time":311447,"text":"If we take all the Amazon,"},{"time":316642,"text":"which is a very large area,"},{"time":318505,"text":"and add it up to all that water\nthat is released by transpiration,"},{"time":321785,"text":"which is the sweat of the forest,"},{"time":324291,"text":"we'll get to an incredible number:"},{"time":326985,"text":"20 billion metric tons of water."},{"time":329781,"text":"In one day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331375,"text":"Do you know how much that is?"},{"time":333562,"text":"The Amazon River,\nthe largest river on Earth,"},{"time":336122,"text":"one fifth of all the fresh water"},{"time":337703,"text":"that leaves the continents of the\nwhole world and ends up in the oceans,"},{"time":341152,"text":"dumps 17 billion metric tons\nof water a day in the Atlantic Ocean."},{"time":345562,"text":"This river of vapor"},{"time":346811,"text":"that comes up from the forest\nand goes into the atmosphere"},{"time":349706,"text":"is greater than the Amazon River."},{"time":351310,"text":"Just to give you an idea."},{"time":353187,"text":"If we could take a gigantic kettle,"},{"time":356743,"text":"the kind you could plug into\na power socket, an electric one,"},{"time":359642,"text":"and put those 20 billion\nmetric tons of water in it,"},{"time":362140,"text":"how much power would you need\nto have this water evaporated?"},{"time":365490,"text":"Any idea? A really big kettle."},{"time":368247,"text":"A gigantic kettle, right?"},{"time":370432,"text":"50 thousand Itaipus."},{"time":372518,"text":"Itaipu is still the largest\nhydroelectric plant in the world."},{"time":376264,"text":"and Brazil is very proud of it"},{"time":377937,"text":"because it provides more \nthan 30 percent of the power"},{"time":380136,"text":"that is consumed in Brazil."},{"time":382093,"text":"And the Amazon is here,\ndoing this for free."},{"time":386785,"text":"It's a vivid and extremely powerful plant,\nproviding environmental services."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394047,"text":"Related to this subject,"},{"time":395608,"text":"we are going to talk about\nwhat I call the paradox of chance,"},{"time":398596,"text":"which is curious."},{"time":400764,"text":"If you look at the world map --"},{"time":402476,"text":"it's easy to see this --"},{"time":403835,"text":"you'll see that there are forests\nin the equatorial zone,"},{"time":406904,"text":"and deserts are organized\nat 30 degrees north latitude,"},{"time":410116,"text":"30 degrees south latitude, aligned."},{"time":413199,"text":"Look over there, in the southern\nhemisphere, the Atacama;"},{"time":416243,"text":"Namibia and Kalahari in Africa;\nthe Australian desert."},{"time":418840,"text":"In the northern hemisphere,\nthe Sahara, Sonoran, etc."},{"time":421994,"text":"There is an exception, and it's curious:"},{"time":426433,"text":"It's the quadrangle that ranges from\nCuiabá to Buenos Aires,"},{"time":429520,"text":"and from São Paulo to the Andes."},{"time":431323,"text":"This quadrangle\nwas supposed to be a desert."},{"time":434437,"text":"It's on the line of deserts."},{"time":436746,"text":"Why isn't it? That's why\nI call it the paradox of chance."},{"time":440010,"text":"What do we have in South America\nthat is different?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":444279,"text":"If we could use the analogy"},{"time":446448,"text":"of the blood circulating in our bodies,"},{"time":450580,"text":"like the water\ncirculating in the landscape,"},{"time":453662,"text":"we see that rivers are veins,"},{"time":457788,"text":"they drain the landscape,\nthey drain the tissue of nature."},{"time":462333,"text":"Where are the arteries?"},{"time":464288,"text":"Any guess?"},{"time":466323,"text":"What takes --"},{"time":468139,"text":"How does water get to irrigate\nthe tissues of nature"},{"time":473402,"text":"and bring everything back through rivers?"},{"time":476585,"text":"There is a new type of river,"},{"time":479606,"text":"which originates in the blue sea,"},{"time":482897,"text":"which flows through the green ocean --"},{"time":486247,"text":"it not only flows, but it is also\npumped by the green ocean --"},{"time":489244,"text":"and then it falls on our land."},{"time":492299,"text":"All our economy, that quadrangle,"},{"time":494507,"text":"70 percent of South America's \nGDP comes from that area."},{"time":499037,"text":"It depends on this river."},{"time":500675,"text":"This river flows invisibly above us."},{"time":502727,"text":"We are floating here\non this floating hotel,"},{"time":504915,"text":"on one of the largest rivers on Earth,\nthe Negro River."},{"time":507870,"text":"It's a bit dry and rough,\nbut we are floating here,"},{"time":511259,"text":"and there is this\ninvisible river running above us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514349,"text":"This river has a pulse."},{"time":517516,"text":"Here it is, pulsing."},{"time":519939,"text":"That's why we also talk about the heart."},{"time":522327,"text":"You can see the different seasons there."},{"time":524462,"text":"There's the rainy season. In the Amazon,\nwe used to have two seasons,"},{"time":527823,"text":"the humid season\nand the even more humid season."},{"time":530306,"text":"Now we have a dry season."},{"time":531962,"text":"You can see the river covering that region"},{"time":534671,"text":"which, otherwise, would be a desert.\nAnd it is not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541633,"text":"We, scientists --\nYou see that I'm struggling here"},{"time":545151,"text":"to move my head\nfrom one side to the other."},{"time":547634,"text":"Scientists study how it works, why, etc."},{"time":553031,"text":"and these studies\nare generating a series of discoveries,"},{"time":557718,"text":"which are absolutely fabulous,"},{"time":559290,"text":"to raise our awareness of the wealth,"},{"time":562283,"text":"the complexity,\nand the wonder that we have,"},{"time":564668,"text":"the symphony we have in this process."},{"time":567649,"text":"One of them is: How is rain formed?"},{"time":569997,"text":"Above the Amazon, there is clean air,"},{"time":573522,"text":"as there is clean air above the ocean."},{"time":575440,"text":"The blue sea has clean air above it\nand forms pretty few clouds;"},{"time":578493,"text":"there's almost no rain there."},{"time":579952,"text":"The green ocean has the same clean air,\nbut forms a lot of rain."},{"time":584366,"text":"What is happening here that is different?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":586753,"text":"The forest emits smells,"},{"time":588423,"text":"and these smells are condensation nuclei,"},{"time":591361,"text":"which form drops in the atmosphere."},{"time":593625,"text":"Then, clouds are formed\nand there is torrential rain."},{"time":598503,"text":"The sprinkler of the Garden of Eden."},{"time":601900,"text":"This relation between a living thing,\nwhich is the forest,"},{"time":606712,"text":"and a nonliving thing,\nwhich is the atmosphere,"},{"time":609856,"text":"is ingenious in the Amazon,"},{"time":612133,"text":"because the forest provides\nwater and seeds,"},{"time":617464,"text":"and the atmosphere forms the rain\nand gives water back,"},{"time":620449,"text":"guaranteeing the forest's survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624421,"text":"There are other factors as well."},{"time":625950,"text":"We've talked a little about the heart,"},{"time":627764,"text":"and let's now talk about\nanother function: the liver!"},{"time":630654,"text":"When humid air, high humidity\nand radiation are combined"},{"time":635715,"text":"with these organic compounds,"},{"time":637775,"text":"which I call exogenous vitamin C,\ngenerous vitamin C in the form of gas,"},{"time":643487,"text":"the plants release antioxidants"},{"time":646317,"text":"which react with pollutants."},{"time":648637,"text":"You can rest assured"},{"time":650041,"text":"that you are breathing the purest air\non Earth, here in the Amazon,"},{"time":653538,"text":"because the plants take care\nof this characteristic as well."},{"time":657045,"text":"This benefits the very way plants work,"},{"time":659662,"text":"which is another ingenious cycle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661715,"text":"Speaking of fractals,"},{"time":665569,"text":"and their relation with the way we work,"},{"time":667905,"text":"we can establish other comparisons."},{"time":670493,"text":"As in the upper airways of our lungs,"},{"time":674024,"text":"the air in the Amazon\ngets cleaned up from the excess of dust."},{"time":677736,"text":"The dust in the air that we breathe\nis cleaned by our airways."},{"time":681714,"text":"This keeps the excess of dust\nfrom affecting the rainfall."},{"time":685533,"text":"When there are fires in the Amazon,"},{"time":687380,"text":"the smoke stops the rain, \nit stops raining,"},{"time":690224,"text":"the forest dries up and catches fire."},{"time":692426,"text":"There is another fractal analogy."},{"time":695057,"text":"Like in the veins and arteries,"},{"time":697009,"text":"the rain water is a feedback."},{"time":699805,"text":"It returns to the atmosphere."},{"time":701834,"text":"Like endocrinal glands and hormones,"},{"time":706120,"text":"there are those gases\nwhich I told you about before,"},{"time":708863,"text":"that are formed and released\ninto the atmosphere, like hormones,"},{"time":712495,"text":"which help in the formation of rain."},{"time":715490,"text":"Like the liver and the kidneys,\nas I've said, cleaning the air."},{"time":719435,"text":"And, finally, like the heart:"},{"time":721234,"text":"pumping water from outside, from the sea,"},{"time":726307,"text":"into the forest."},{"time":728179,"text":"We call it the biotic moisture pump,"},{"time":731581,"text":"a new theory that is explained\nin a very simple way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735731,"text":"If there is a desert in the continent"},{"time":738389,"text":"with a nearby sea,"},{"time":740477,"text":"evaporation's greater on the sea,"},{"time":742311,"text":"and it sucks the air above the desert."},{"time":745280,"text":"The desert is trapped in this condition.\nIt will always be dry."},{"time":748762,"text":"If you have\nthe opposite situation, a forest,"},{"time":751528,"text":"the evaporation, as we showed,\nis much greater, because of the trees,"},{"time":755266,"text":"and this relation is reversed."},{"time":756978,"text":"The air above the sea\nis sucked into the continent"},{"time":759331,"text":"and humidity is imported."},{"time":762179,"text":"This satellite image\nwas taken one month ago —"},{"time":766676,"text":"that's Manaus down there,\nwe're down there —"},{"time":769063,"text":"and it shows this process."},{"time":770418,"text":"It's not a common little river\nthat flows into a canal."},{"time":773462,"text":"It's a mighty river\nthat irrigates South America,"},{"time":778192,"text":"among other things."},{"time":780016,"text":"This image shows those paths,"},{"time":782333,"text":"all the hurricanes\nthat have been recorded."},{"time":785638,"text":"You can see that, in the red square,\nthere hardly are any hurricanes."},{"time":790208,"text":"That is no accident."},{"time":791786,"text":"This pump that sucks\nthe moisture into the continent"},{"time":795250,"text":"also speeds up the air above the sea,"},{"time":797485,"text":"and this prevents hurricane formations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801053,"text":"To close this part and sum up,"},{"time":805645,"text":"I'd like to talk about\nsomething a little different."},{"time":808265,"text":"I have several colleagues"},{"time":810225,"text":"who worked in the development\nof these theories."},{"time":812710,"text":"They think, and so do I,"},{"time":816341,"text":"that we can save planet Earth."},{"time":818939,"text":"I'm not talking only about the Amazon."},{"time":821684,"text":"The Amazon teaches us a lesson"},{"time":823809,"text":"on how pristine nature works."},{"time":827845,"text":"We didn't understand\nthese processes before"},{"time":830251,"text":"because the rest of the world\nis messed up."},{"time":833086,"text":"We could understand it here, though."},{"time":834993,"text":"These colleagues propose\nthat, yes, we can"},{"time":838370,"text":"save other areas,"},{"time":840077,"text":"including deserts."},{"time":842172,"text":"If we could establish forests\nin those other areas,"},{"time":845597,"text":"we can reverse climate change,"},{"time":847709,"text":"including global warming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850324,"text":"I have a dear colleague in India,"},{"time":852540,"text":"whose name is Suprabha Seshan,\nand she has a motto."},{"time":855614,"text":"Her motto is,\n\"Gardening back the biosphere,\""},{"time":859928,"text":"\"Reajardinando a biosfera\" in Portuguese."},{"time":862286,"text":"She does a wonderful job\nrebuilding ecosystems."},{"time":865284,"text":"We need to do this."},{"time":867851,"text":"Having closed this quick introduction,"},{"time":872036,"text":"we see the reality that we have out here,"},{"time":875622,"text":"which is drought, this climate change,"},{"time":878632,"text":"things that we already knew."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880515,"text":"I'd like to tell you a short story."},{"time":884649,"text":"Once, about four years ago,"},{"time":888282,"text":"I attended a declamation,\nof a text by Davi Kopenawa,"},{"time":892169,"text":"a wise representative\nof the Yanomami people,"},{"time":895267,"text":"and it went more or less like this:"},{"time":897462,"text":"\"Doesn't the white man know"},{"time":900087,"text":"that, if he destroys the forest,\nthere will be no more rain?"},{"time":903478,"text":"And that, if there's no more rain,"},{"time":905241,"text":"there'll be nothing to drink, or to eat?\""},{"time":908464,"text":"I heard that, and my eyes welled up"},{"time":911145,"text":"and I went, \"Oh, my!"},{"time":912588,"text":"I've been studying this for 20 years,\nwith a super computer,"},{"time":916904,"text":"dozens, thousands of scientists,"},{"time":919034,"text":"and we are starting to get to this\nconclusion, which he already knows!\""},{"time":922712,"text":"A critical point is the Yanomami\nhave never deforested."},{"time":927746,"text":"How could they know the rain would end?"},{"time":930385,"text":"This bugged me and I was befuddled."},{"time":934327,"text":"How could he know that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":935773,"text":"Some months later,\nI met him at another event and said,"},{"time":939536,"text":"\"Davi, how did you know that if the forest\nwas destroyed, there'd be no more rain?\""},{"time":945342,"text":"He replied:\n\"The spirit of the forest told us.\""},{"time":950157,"text":"For me, this was a game changer,"},{"time":954744,"text":"a radical change."},{"time":956447,"text":"I said, \"Gosh!"},{"time":957866,"text":"Why am I doing all this science"},{"time":962105,"text":"to get to a conclusion\nthat he already knows?\""},{"time":965167,"text":"Then, something \nabsolutely critical hit me,"},{"time":971174,"text":"which is,"},{"time":975697,"text":"seeing is believing."},{"time":979932,"text":"Out of sight, out of mind."},{"time":983140,"text":"This is a need the previous speaker\npointed out:"},{"time":987928,"text":"We need to see things --"},{"time":990712,"text":"I mean, we, Western society,"},{"time":992900,"text":"which is becoming global, civilized --"},{"time":995262,"text":"we need to see."},{"time":996665,"text":"If we don't see,\nwe don't register the information."},{"time":999188,"text":"We live in ignorance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1000932,"text":"So, I propose the following --"},{"time":1002822,"text":"of course, the astronomer\nwouldn't like the idea --"},{"time":1005274,"text":"but let's turn the Hubble telescope\nupside down."},{"time":1008130,"text":"And let's make it look down here,"},{"time":1010547,"text":"rather than to the far reaches\nof the universe."},{"time":1012797,"text":"The universe is wonderful,"},{"time":1014539,"text":"but we have a practical reality,"},{"time":1016914,"text":"which is we live in an unknown cosmos,"},{"time":1020734,"text":"and we're ignorant about it."},{"time":1022117,"text":"We're trampling on this wonderful cosmos"},{"time":1025787,"text":"that shelters us and houses us."},{"time":1027826,"text":"Talk to any astrophysicist."},{"time":1029492,"text":"The Earth is a statistical improbability."},{"time":1032778,"text":"The stability and comfort that we enjoy,\ndespite the droughts of the Negro River,"},{"time":1036976,"text":"and all the heat and cold\nand typhoons, etc.,"},{"time":1039939,"text":"there is nothing like it in the universe,\nthat we know of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042673,"text":"Then, let's turn Hubble in our direction,"},{"time":1044922,"text":"and let's look at the Earth."},{"time":1049431,"text":"Let's start with the Amazon!"},{"time":1051541,"text":"Let's dive,"},{"time":1052920,"text":"let's reach out the reality\nwe live in every day,"},{"time":1057466,"text":"and look carefully at it,\nsince that's what we need."},{"time":1060693,"text":"Davi Kopenawa doesn't need this."},{"time":1062624,"text":"He has something already\nthat I think I missed."},{"time":1065003,"text":"I was educated by television."},{"time":1066678,"text":"I think that I missed this,"},{"time":1068589,"text":"an ancestral record,"},{"time":1070484,"text":"a valuation of what I don't know,\nwhat I haven't seen."},{"time":1074864,"text":"He is not a doubting Thomas."},{"time":1076986,"text":"He believes, \nwith veneration and reverence,"},{"time":1080192,"text":"in what his ancestors\nand the spirits taught him."},{"time":1083563,"text":"We can't do it,\nso let's look into the forest."},{"time":1086337,"text":"Even with Hubble up there --"},{"time":1089543,"text":"this is a bird's-eye view, right?"},{"time":1091888,"text":"Even when this happens,"},{"time":1093758,"text":"we also see something that we don't know."},{"time":1096862,"text":"The Spanish called it the green inferno."},{"time":1099148,"text":"If you go out there\ninto the bushes and get lost,"},{"time":1102018,"text":"and, let's say, if you head west,"},{"time":1104256,"text":"it's 900 kilometers to Colombia,"},{"time":1106225,"text":"and another 1,000 to somewhere else."},{"time":1108162,"text":"So, you can figure out\nwhy they called it the green inferno."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1111309,"text":"But go and look at what is in there."},{"time":1114563,"text":"It is a live carpet."},{"time":1116054,"text":"Each color you see is a tree species."},{"time":1118350,"text":"Each tree, each tree top,"},{"time":1120135,"text":"has up to 10,000 species of insects in it,"},{"time":1124691,"text":"let alone the millions of species\nof fungi, bacteria, etc."},{"time":1128749,"text":"All invisible."},{"time":1130401,"text":"All of it is an even stranger cosmos to us"},{"time":1133645,"text":"than the galaxies billions\nof light years away from the Earth,"},{"time":1136554,"text":"which Hubble brings\nto our newspapers everyday."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1140983,"text":"I'm going to end my talk here --"},{"time":1142853,"text":"I have a few seconds left --"},{"time":1144664,"text":"by showing you this wonderful being."},{"time":1146708,"text":"When we see the morpho butterfly\nin the forest,"},{"time":1149596,"text":"we feel like someone's left open\nthe door to heaven,"},{"time":1152431,"text":"and this creature escaped from there,\nbecause it's so beautiful."},{"time":1155632,"text":"However, I cannot finish"},{"time":1158017,"text":"without showing you a tech side."},{"time":1160548,"text":"We are tech-arrogant."},{"time":1163758,"text":"We deprive nature of its technology."},{"time":1167049,"text":"A robotic hand is technological,"},{"time":1168773,"text":"mine is biological,"},{"time":1170150,"text":"and we don't think about it anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1171913,"text":"Let's then look at the morpho butterfly,"},{"time":1174015,"text":"an example of an invisible\ntechnological competence of life,"},{"time":1179456,"text":"which is at the very heart of our\npossibility of surviving on this planet,"},{"time":1184083,"text":"and let's zoom in on it.\nAgain, Hubble is there."},{"time":1186348,"text":"Let's get into the butterfly's wings."},{"time":1188262,"text":"Scholars have tried to explain:\nWhy is it blue?"},{"time":1192465,"text":"Let's zoom in on it."},{"time":1193935,"text":"What you see is that the architecture\nof the invisible humiliates"},{"time":1199011,"text":"the best architects in the world."},{"time":1202043,"text":"All of this on a tiny scale."},{"time":1204440,"text":"Besides its beauty and functioning,\nthere is another side to it."},{"time":1207968,"text":"In nature,"},{"time":1210166,"text":"all that is organized in extraordinary\nstructures has a function."},{"time":1214529,"text":"This function of the morpho butterfly —\nit is not blue;"},{"time":1219019,"text":"it does not have blue pigments."},{"time":1220673,"text":"It has photonic crystals on its surface,\naccording to people who studied it,"},{"time":1224717,"text":"which are extremely \nsophisticated crystals."},{"time":1226968,"text":"Our technology had\nnothing like that at the time."},{"time":1230427,"text":"Hitachi has now made a monitor"},{"time":1233208,"text":"that uses this technology,"},{"time":1234563,"text":"and it is used in optical fibers\nto transmit --"},{"time":1236940,"text":"Janine Benyus, who's been here several\ntimes, talks about it: biomimetics."},{"time":1241350,"text":"My time's up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1242702,"text":"Then, I'll wrap it up with\nwhat is at the base of this capacity,"},{"time":1248012,"text":"of this competence of biodiversity,"},{"time":1250584,"text":"producing all these wonderful services:"},{"time":1253006,"text":"the living cell."},{"time":1254913,"text":"It is a structure with a few microns,\nwhich is an internal wonder."},{"time":1258427,"text":"There are TED Talks about it.\nI won't talk much longer,"},{"time":1261454,"text":"but each person in this room,\nincluding myself,"},{"time":1264628,"text":"has 100 trillion of these\nmicromachines in their body,"},{"time":1268319,"text":"so that we can enjoy well-being."},{"time":1271159,"text":"Imagine what is out there\nin the Amazon forest:"},{"time":1273916,"text":"100 trillion. This is greater\nthan the number of stars in the sky."},{"time":1277927,"text":"And we are not aware of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1279985,"text":"Thank you so much. (Applause)"}]}]}